        <div class="panel-heading"><h3 class="blue-title">What is ROI?</h3></div>
        <div class="panel-body"><h1><i class="fa fa-percent fa-3x"></i></h1>
        <p>Return On Investment (ROI) is calculated by the total returns divided by the total amount bet (total turnover). Note this percentage is not an indication of total profit of initial investment, as your initial investment will be turned over countless times. For total return on investment, simply look at Units won (1unit = 1% of initial investment). Puntsquad aims to achieve a minimum of 5% ROI on all products, which means that you, the punter can expect to make 5 cents off every dollar you bet on average in the long run.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="panel panel-default betting_guide_row2">
        <div class="panel-heading"><h3 class="blue-title">What is Variance?</h3></div>
        <div class="panel-body"><h1><i class="fa fa-line-chart fa-3x"></i></h1>
        <p>Variance can either be your worst enemy or your best friend. A coin-flip should be 50/50. If you flip 10 times in a perfect world, you would get 5 heads and 5 tails. However real-life is not like this. We will do our best to offer tips that SHOULD turn you a profit in the long run, but variance could mean you will make a loss on those tips as nothing is guaranteed. Here at Puntsquad, we ask all our members to focus on the long-run, and to ride out the short-term variances that may arise. As of 13/10/16, our largest downswing has been -65 units meaning if you had started at the peak, you would have lost 65% of your initial investment. Such things do happen, but have faith in the models to rebound.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
